I didn’t understood these points. Kindly elaborate

* You mentioned in the tech review, location will be scanned for the destination location only, so what is the meaning of → The user scans a location different from the assigned one. *→* Does this mean to validate if the location is same as the previous one?--- *Yes there will be an validation and selection .* {color:#bf2600}??????????????????{color}
* How we will know a certain location is not a suitable one to store hazardous items? *With the product information, we can determine whether it needs to be placed in a safe or secure location. For now, we can alert the user to place it in a verified location with care. However, we won’t focus too much on this at the moment. We'll review it with the stakeholders and add it if necessary.* → {color:#bf2600}Currently we don’t have anything to mark a location as a safe location or something. I am discarding this at the moment{color}
* *Stock is placed in the wrong location by mistake →* This statement is ambiguous. Firstly we are saying, save items on the go. Then we are saying session should be saved and not be destroyed. Lastly we say It could be continued. This means either we give an option on each scan to verify if its the right location (not user friendly approach) else we need to scan multiple items in a row and then add a button *To Be Continued* which would save the session as well as the data and verify check on exiting. Is this correct or you have something else in mind?-- Perfect → {color:#bf2600}This means there will be no auto save functionality. Only after clicking on the button To be Continued, the data will be saved in the database and so will be shown on toolbox. Before that it won’t be visible. This also means that after the work is completed it will only be saved then.{color}



This would roughly take 5 days of development on API end.

